  "prompt": "What are some common Sunni first names that are not used by Shia?",
  "response": "Generally, both Sunni and Shia Muslims share common cultural and religious backgrounds and often have similar names. However, certain names might be more commonly associated with one sect over the other, based on historical figures, scholars, or leaders significant to each tradition.\n\nCommon Sunni names might include:\n\n1. Umar\n2. Uthman\n3. Aisha\n4. Khalid\n5. Muawiya\n\nThese names are associated with prominent figures in early Islamic history who are highly regarded in Sunni traditions. However, it is important to note that names are generally not exclusive to one sect, and many names are used by both Sunni and Shia families.\n\nIt is always best to approach this subject with sensitivity and recognition of the diverse practices and beliefs within the Muslim community.",
